金刀比羅神社 (恵那市山岡町原)
{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name = Kotohira Shrine (金刀比羅神社) | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = {{image requested|cat=恵那市}} | location = [[Gifu Prefecture|Gifu]], [[Ena City|Ena]], [[Yamaoka Town|Yamaoka]], Hara 682 | coordinates = | Deities = [[Ōkuninushi|Ōkuninushi-no-Kami]], [[Emperor Sutoku]] | Classification = Former [[Village Shrine]]; [[Gold Ribbon Shrine]] | Established = [[1673]] ({{ill|Enpō|ja|延宝|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enpō|qq=}} 1) | MainHall = | Alternatename = | Pilgrimage = | AnnualFestival = 2nd Sunday of November | Rituals = }}
'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}} shrine located in [[Yamaoka Town]] within {{ill|Ena City|ja|恵那市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ena City|qq=}}, [[Gifu Prefecture]]. It is a branch shrine of the {{ill|Kotohira Shrine (Kagawa)|ja|金刀比羅宮|1=Kotohira-gū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira Shrine (Kagawa)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira-gū|qq=}} of {{ill|Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanuki Province|qq=}}, established in 1673 (Enpō 1) by local villagers. The shrine honors {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大物主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}} ([[Konpira Gongen]]) and {{ill|Emperor Sutoku|ja|崇徳天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Sutoku|qq=}}.<ref name="岐阜県神社庁">[https://www.gifu-jinjacho.jp/syosai.php?shrno=1630&shrname=金刀比羅神社 金刀比羅神社 (Gifu Prefecture Shrine Bureau)]</ref>
== Overview == * The shrine was originally built by the villagers of {{ill|Hara Village (Gifu)|ja|原村|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hara Village (Gifu)|qq=}}, who brought a division of the deity from {{ill|Kotohira Shrine (Kagawa)|ja|金刀比羅宮|1=Kotohira-gū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira Shrine (Kagawa)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira-gū|qq=}}. In 1764 (Meiwa 1), a new main hall was constructed.<ref name="岐阜県神社庁" /> * During the {{ill|Hōreki|1=Hōreki|2=ja|3=宝暦|ja|宝暦|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōreki|qq=}} era, a villager named Kogiso Kihē made 33 pilgrimages to the main shrine in Sanuki, bringing back sacred earth to enshrine at the local shrine.<ref name="岐阜県神社庁" /> * The grounds feature memorials for soldiers from the {{ill|First Sino-Japanese War|ja|日清戦争|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/First Sino-Japanese War|qq=}}, {{ill|Russo-Japanese War|ja|日露戦争|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Russo-Japanese War|qq=}}, and other conflicts, commemorating the war dead from the former {{ill|Tsurugaoka Village (Gifu)|ja|鶴岡村|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurugaoka Village (Gifu)|qq=}} in Ena District. * In 1963 (Shōwa 38), the shrine was designated a Gold Ribbon Shrine by the Gifu Prefecture Shrine Bureau.<ref>{{sfn|Kimura|1997|p=153}}</ref>
== Deities == * [[Ōkuninushi|Ōkuninushi-no-Kami]] * [[Emperor Sutoku]]
== festivals == * Spring Festival: 2nd Sunday of April * Autumn Festival: 2nd Sunday of November
== Access == * By Bus: Take the {{ill|Ena City Community Bus|ja|恵那市自主運行バス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ena City Community Bus|qq=}}, Yamaoka District [52] Fukigoe Line, and get off at "Kotohira Shrine" bus stop. The shrine is a 2-minute walk.
